    <dcterms:title>In Roanoke, Va., WSLS-TV reporter Jim Walsh interviews Virginia Attorney General J. Lindsay Almond on anti-integration efforts in the state</dcterms:title><dcterms:description>In Roanoke, Va., WSLS-TV reporter Jim Walsh interviews Virginia Attorney General J. Lindsay Almond regarding efforts to avoid school integration in Virginia. Almond predicts that Governor Thomas B. Stanley will face a long and difficult battle in his efforts to pass anti-integration legislation, but he expresses confidence in the governor's resolve and determination, asserting his own unequivocal opposition to integration.</dcterms:description><dcterms:created>1956-08-15</dcterms:created>
